3 REASONS $AVGO EARNINGS REACTION WENT NEGATIVE

1. The backlog quality suddenly looked less secured
Many investors treated the OpenAI relationship like a typical binding hyperscaler contract but Broadcom‚Äôs ‚Äúmultiyear journey‚Äù language in the Q&A made it sound more like a general framework than a firm capacity commitment.

2. The revenue timing moved far out
Management made it clear that meaningful XPU revenue does not show up in 2026 & instead ramps in 2027‚Äì2029 and long-dated revenue always carries higher risk so this needs to be discounted.

3. Supply constraints cap 2026 upside
Broadcom disclosed a $72B backlog with 18-month lead times which signals they're already running at full capacity & cannot accelerate deliveries even if demand spikes so that limits how much they can monetize the hottest phase of hyperscaler AI spend.
